y have restarted or the timestamp doesn't indicate termination. The critical crons (ed2d0b5d and 6f3323ef) are both running, the Agent Status cron was updated at 13:24, and there are no new failures to report.\\n\\nLooking at the previous state, the Lead Direct session has now ended at 13:15 UTC, whereas before it was still marked as running. That appears to be the only change between the two states. Let me double-check that this is the only difference by reviewing the previous session list to make sure I'm not missing anything. I'm noticing that the cron:e7885813 (Agent Status) session appears in the current list with `abortedLastRun: false` and a fresh session ID, indicating it restarted at 13:24. Looking at the main session messages, it successfully delivered the report at 13:24 and processed feedback, though the Agent Status cron itself shows some aborted attempts that don't affect the overall status.\\n\\nChecking against the last recorded state, the main session is still marked as \\\"done\\\" in the heartbeat data, so this doesn't represent a change. The Lead Direct session was also \\\"done\\\" at 13:15 UTC, which is consistent with the previous heartbeat.\\n\\nThe critical monitoring sessions are all running as expected: the 5p crons for both QLHV and DTLX, plus the Agent Status cron. All systems operational, pipeline healthy, no blockers.\\n\\nSilent exit — nothing to report.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"**Silent exit.** Comparing current sessions against `heartbeat-state.json` (last heartbeat: 13:28 UTC):\\n\\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` (5p QLHV): running ✅ — normal tick\\n- `cron:6f3323ef` (5p DTLX): running ✅ — normal tick\\n- `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status): running ✅ — alive (updatedAt 13:24)\\n- All other sessions: consistent with last state ✅\\n\\nNo new failures, no blockers, no state changes. Pipeline stable.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n        